ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Norovirus infections now occur throughout the world and are an
inevitable accompaniment of winter in temperate climates, as their
colloquial description "winter vomiting disease" implies. In England
and Wales, for example, 2607 outbreaks were registered in 2005.
Schools and hospitals are especially vulnerable. Illness is
self-limiting are rarely has serious consequences. Consequently
ProMED-mail will no longer report individual outbreaks of norovirus
infection except in specific circumstances such as on board cruise
ships or where there is appearance of a new serotype of a new virus.
The above report is posted because of the implied connection with the
city of Christchurch, where there has been both a restaurant-related
outbreak of norovirus infection and an unrelated outbreak of
hepatitis A in a child-care centre. - Mod.CP]
